Male genitalia (
Figs. 14–20
).
Truncus changing direction abruptly at distal part (
Fig. 14
). Ventral plate of penis strongly leaned against truncus (
Figs. 14
), with wide and shallow V-cleft (
Figs. 15–16
), guitar-shaped (
Figs. 15–16
